---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const seo = {
  title: '10 Best Instagram Scheduling Tools in 2026 (Reels, Stories & Carousels)',
  description: 'We tested 10 Instagram scheduling tools for Reels, Stories, and carousel support. Real pricing, feature comparison, and workflow recommendations. Updated March 2026.',
  canonical: 'https://thestacc.com/best/best-instagram-scheduling-tools/',
  ogImage: '/og/best-best-instagram-scheduling-tools.webp',
  schemaData: [
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://thestacc.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Best", "item": "https://thestacc.com/best/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Best Instagram Scheduling Tools", "item": "https://thestacc.com/best/best-instagram-scheduling-tools/" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "ItemList",
      "name": "10 Best Instagram Scheduling Tools in 2026",
      "itemListOrder": "https://schema.org/ItemListOrderDescending",
      "numberOfItems": 10,
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Later" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Buffer" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Pallyy" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "SocialBee" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 5, "name": "Sked Social" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 6, "name": "Iconosquare" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 7, "name": "Planly" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 8, "name": "SocialPilot" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 9, "name": "Tailwind" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 10, "name": "Hootsuite" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the best free Instagram scheduling tool in 2026?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Buffer offers the simplest free experience with 3 channels and auto-publish for Reels. Pallyy provides a visual grid planner with 15 monthly posts free — three times Later's free tier offering. Both auto-publish to Instagram without manual steps." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can you schedule Instagram Reels in advance?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. All 10 tools in this list support Reels scheduling with auto-publish. In 2026, Reels auto-publishing is standard across major scheduling platforms. You schedule the Reel, set a time, and it publishes automatically." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How often should you post on Instagram in 2026?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "3–5 feed posts weekly is the minimum to maintain algorithmic visibility. The optimal 2026 content mix is 60–70% Reels, 20–30% carousels, and 10% single images. Daily Stories maintain visibility between feed posts. Consistency matters more than volume." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can you schedule Instagram Stories?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Most tools support Stories with either auto-publish or push notifications. Sked Social, Later, Buffer, and SocialBee auto-publish Stories directly without manual steps. Tailwind does not support Stories auto-publishing." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the cheapest Instagram scheduling tool?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Planly starts at $15/month with Reels and Stories support. Buffer Essentials costs $6/month per channel, making it cheaper for single accounts. Both Buffer and Pallyy offer usable free plans with auto-publishing included." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Does theStacc handle Instagram automatically?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. theStacc's Social Media module publishes 30 posts per month across Instagram, LinkedIn, X, and Facebook for $49/month — no scheduling tool setup or management required. Content is created and published automatically based on your blog content and brand voice." }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
};
---
<BaseLayout seo={seo}>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero-section">
    <a href="/best/" class="hero-pill">
      <span class="pill-dot"></span>
      <span>Best of 2026 · Updated this quarter</span>
      <span class="pill-arrow">→</span>
    </a>
    <h1 class="h-display">10 Best <span class="accent">Instagram Scheduling Tools</span> in 2026 (Reels, Stories &amp; Carousels)</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">Instagram engagement dropped 24% year-over-year in 2025. Reels now average 2.05% engagement — the highest of any format. We tested 10 scheduling tools for Reels, Stories, and carousel auto-publishing, visual grid planning, and analytics depth. Here's what's actually worth using.</p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Auto-publish to Instagram with theStacc — $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
      <a href="#ranked-list" class="btn btn-secondary">See the full ranking</a>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span><strong>10 tools</strong> tested and compared</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span><strong>Reels, Stories, carousels</strong> — all formats evaluated</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span>Last updated <strong>Q1 2026</strong></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- QUICK VERDICT -->
  <section class="modules-bento">
    <div class="modules-tabs-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Quick verdict · 4 picks</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">If you only read one section, <span class="accent">read this one.</span></h2>
      <p class="lede">Four picks for four buyer types. Full ranked list and comparison table below.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bento-grid">
      <a class="bento-card bento-feature" href="#service-1">
        <div class="bento-num">01</div>
        <div class="bento-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Best overall: Later</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">Visual grid planner, <span class="accent">auto-publish for all formats</span>, Linkin.bio landing page, and solid analytics from $25/month.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Built specifically for Instagram. Drag-and-drop feed preview lets you see how posts look in your grid before scheduling. Auto-publishes Reels, feed posts, carousels, and Stories. Analytics break down engagement by content type. Free plan with 5 posts to test.</p>
        <ul class="bento-list">
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Visual grid planner — preview feed layout before publishing</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Auto-publishes Reels, Stories, carousels, and feed posts</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Linkin.bio landing page included</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Free plan · Paid from $25/month</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="bento-mock">
          <div class="bento-mock-bar">
            <div class="bento-mock-meta">LATER · #1 OVERALL · FROM $25/MO</div>
            <span class="bento-mock-pulse"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="bento-mock-title">Visual grid · All formats · Analytics · Linkin.bio</div>
          <div class="bento-mock-tags">
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">$25/mo</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag">Free plan</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">Grid planner</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>

      <a class="bento-card" href="#service-2">
        <div class="bento-num">02</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Best free option: Buffer</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">3 channels, <span class="accent">auto-publish Reels</span>, and the cleanest scheduling interface — free forever.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Minimal interface. Fast post composition. AI caption variations. Free plan covers 10 posts per channel. The simplest starting point for anyone new to Instagram scheduling.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>

      <a class="bento-card" href="#service-8">
        <div class="bento-num">08</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Best for agencies: SocialPilot</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">White-label dashboards, <span class="accent">500-post bulk scheduling via CSV</span>, and client approval workflows from $30/month.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Bulk scheduling, white-label reporting, and client management — the agency-focused tool in the category. No free plan but a 14-day trial.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW WE TESTED -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">How we tested</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">Auto-publishing for Reels is now standard. <span class="accent">Differentiation is in the details.</span></h2>
      <p>In 2026, all major schedulers support Reels auto-publishing. We focused on the features that actually separate tools: visual grid planning, AI caption generation, analytics depth, and whether Stories auto-publish without a push notification workaround. Instagram engagement dropped 24% YoY in 2025 — the right tool helps you maintain visibility in a declining-reach environment.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we measured</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">5 criteria. Same scorecard across all 10.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Reels auto-publish alone isn't a differentiator in 2026.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Reels and Stories auto-publish</h4>
              <p>Does it publish without a push notification or manual step? True auto-publish only.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Visual grid planner</h4>
              <p>Can you preview how your feed looks before scheduling? Drag-and-drop layout tools.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Instagram-specific analytics</h4>
              <p>Engagement by content type, optimal posting times, and reach data.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>AI features</h4>
              <p>Caption generation, hashtag suggestions, and AI-powered timing recommendations.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Cost per channel at scale</h4>
              <p>True monthly cost managing 5–10 accounts, not just single-profile pricing.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">Key 2026 Instagram stats</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Format and cadence benchmarks for 2026.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Use these numbers to calibrate your scheduling strategy.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">2.05%</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Reels engagement rate — highest of any format</h4>
              <p>Prioritize Reels in your content mix. 60–70% of posts should be video in 2026.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">1.92%</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Carousel engagement rate — second strongest</h4>
              <p>20–30% carousels in your mix. They get swiped, which signals engagement to the algorithm.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">3–5</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Minimum weekly feed posts to maintain visibility</h4>
              <p>Consistency matters more than volume. Missing weeks hurts algorithmic reach.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">-24%</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Year-over-year engagement drop (2025)</h4>
              <p>The right content mix and scheduling cadence matter more than they did 2 years ago.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STATS -->
  <section>
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">10<span class="accent"></span></div><div class="stat-label">Scheduling tools tested</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">2.05<span class="accent">%</span></div><div class="stat-label">Reels engagement rate · best format 2026</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">-24<span class="accent">%</span></div><div class="stat-label">YoY engagement decline · 2025</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">$6<span class="accent">/mo</span></div><div class="stat-label">Cheapest paid option · Buffer per channel</div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RANKED LIST -->
  <section class="problem-section" id="ranked-list">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">The full ranked list</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">10 Instagram scheduling tools, <span class="accent">ranked by Instagram-specific value.</span></h2>
      <p>Each entry: rank, name, price, who it fits, verdict, pros, and one honest con.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-1">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#1 · FROM $25/MO · FREE PLAN</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Later — Best overall Instagram scheduling tool</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For small businesses and creators that want visual grid planning, all-format auto-publishing, and Instagram-specific analytics in one tool.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Later was built specifically for Instagram before it expanded to other platforms. The visual grid planner lets you drag and drop posts to preview exactly how your feed will look before anything goes live — a feature that matters when feed aesthetics drive follower decisions. Auto-publishing covers all formats: Reels, Stories, carousels, and single images. Analytics break down engagement by content type and surface optimal posting windows. Linkin.bio creates a shoppable landing page from your Instagram link. Free plan allows 5 posts per profile per month.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Visual grid planner — drag-and-drop feed preview before scheduling</h4>
              <p>See how new posts affect your overall grid aesthetic before publishing. No other tool at this price does this better.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Auto-publishes all formats — Reels, Stories, carousels, and feed posts</h4>
              <p>No push notifications, no manual steps. Everything goes live on schedule.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Engagement analytics by content type included</h4>
              <p>See which format — Reel, carousel, single image — performs best for your specific audience.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✗</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Honest con: 5-post free plan limit, inbox limited to Instagram/Facebook/TikTok</h4>
              <p>Five posts per month won't cover a real posting cadence. Full analytics require the paid Growth tier at $33/month.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div style="margin-top: 24px;">
          <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Auto-publish to Instagram with theStacc $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-2" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#2 · $6/MO/CHANNEL · FREE PLAN</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Buffer — Best free Instagram scheduling tool</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">The cleanest, simplest scheduling experience — free for 3 channels with Reels auto-publish and a landing page builder.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Buffer has the most minimal and intuitive interface in the category. Post composition is fast, AI caption variations generate on request, and a calendar view shows your scheduled content. The free plan covers 3 channels with 10 posts each and auto-publishes Reels. A landing page builder is included. The honest gap: no visual grid planner, basic analytics compared to dedicated Instagram tools, and the 10-post per channel limit on the free plan restricts active posting cadences.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Cleanest interface in the category — minimal, fast, no learning curve</h4><p>If you find most tools overwhelming, Buffer is where to start.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Free plan covers 3 channels with Reels auto-publish</h4><p>Genuinely useful free tier — not just a demo. Auto-publishes without push notifications.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>AI caption variations included</h4><p>Generate multiple caption options from a single prompt. Useful for testing tone and messaging.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: no visual grid planner, basic analytics</h4><p>You can't preview your feed layout. Analytics are limited to basic engagement data — no content-type breakdown.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-3" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#3 · $25/MO · 15 FREE POSTS</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Pallyy — Best for creators wanting a free grid planner</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Instagram-first platform with a visual grid planner and 15 free posts per month — the most generous free tier in this list.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Pallyy combines a visual grid planner (similar to Later) with a 15-post free tier — three times what Later offers. Built primarily for creators and freelancers who want Instagram-specific planning tools without paying immediately. Bio link pages are included. Basic analytics available on the free tier. The paid plan at $25/month per social set unlocks unlimited posts. Less established than Later or Buffer, but the free tier is genuinely the most useful in this list for someone testing the category.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>15 free posts per month — most generous free tier in this list</h4><p>Three times Later's free tier. Actually covers a real posting cadence at 3–4 posts per week.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Visual grid planner included on free tier</h4><p>Later's grid planner feature, available without paying. The main reason to choose Pallyy over Buffer.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Bio link pages included</h4><p>Turn the single Instagram link into a landing page. Same functionality as Later's Linkin.bio.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: less established platform, no team collaboration, one social set on free tier</h4><p>Newer platform means less third-party integrations and a smaller community. No team features on any tier.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-4" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#4 · FROM $29/MO · 14-DAY TRIAL</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">SocialBee — Best for AI caption writing</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">AI Copilot generates captions and schedules automatically, with content recycling for evergreen posts and team approval workflows.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">SocialBee differentiates on AI caption generation through its Copilot feature — it creates a full content strategy including captions, hashtags, and scheduling based on your brand inputs. Evergreen content recycling automatically reshares high-performing posts. Visual grid planner helps with feed aesthetics. Team approval workflows let multiple people review before anything publishes. The 14-day trial replaces a free tier, and the $29/month starting price is the steepest entry point among tools with free alternatives.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>AI Copilot generates captions and schedule from brand inputs</h4><p>The most sophisticated AI caption generation in this list. Goes beyond single-caption generation to full content strategy.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Content recycling for evergreen posts</h4><p>Automatically reshares high-performing content on a rotation. Useful for accounts with valuable older posts.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Team approval workflows before publishing</h4><p>Multi-person review before anything goes live. Better than most tools at this price for collaborative accounts.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: no free plan, complex interface, higher entry price</h4><p>The interface has a steeper learning curve than Later or Buffer. 14-day trial only — no ongoing free option.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-5" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#5 · FROM $59/MO · 7-DAY TRIAL</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Sked Social — Best for complete Stories auto-publishing</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">The only tool that auto-publishes Stories with link stickers without manual steps — true full-format automation for Instagram.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Sked Social's differentiator is Stories automation. Most tools require a push notification for Stories. Sked auto-publishes Stories with link stickers — including the URL tap-through — without any manual step. Drag-and-drop grid planner and a built-in image editor are included. Hashtag manager stores and applies hashtag groups. The price starts at $59/month for one account, which is steep compared to Later and Buffer, but the Stories automation justifies it if you rely on daily Story posting.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Auto-publishes Stories with link stickers — the only tool in this list that does this</h4><p>No push notification, no manual step. True Stories automation including tap-through URLs.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Drag-and-drop grid planner with built-in image editor</h4><p>Edit images inside the tool without switching to Canva or Photoshop.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Hashtag manager for organized hashtag group storage</h4><p>Store, categorize, and apply hashtag sets without typing them out every time.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: $59/month starting price, no free plan, less polished interface</h4><p>Expensive for single accounts. The interface feels less refined than Later or Buffer. 7-day trial only.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-6" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#6 · FROM $49/MO · 14-DAY TRIAL</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Iconosquare — Best for deep Instagram analytics</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Comprehensive engagement data, competitor benchmarking, audience-specific optimal timing, and visual scheduling calendar.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Iconosquare leads the category on analytics depth. Engagement tracking breaks down by content type, format, posting time, and hashtag group. Competitor benchmarking shows how your metrics compare to similar accounts. Audience-specific optimal timing identifies when your specific followers are online — not generic industry averages. Scheduling calendar provides a clean visual overview. At $49/month starting, the premium is for analytics rather than scheduling capability. Scheduling features are competent but not Instagram-first the way Later and Pallyy are.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Deepest analytics in category — engagement by content type, timing, and hashtag</h4><p>Makes it clear what's working and why — down to specific post types and publishing windows.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Competitor benchmarking included</h4><p>See how your engagement rate compares to similar accounts. Useful for identifying gaps.</p></div></li>
